page.title: 10STANBRIDGE VILLAGE
page.content: The village of Stanbridge is one small group of houses.It has a church and a bus stop.Five worker's cottages are tucked away between some large trees. Most of Stanbridge is owned by Mrs.Gibson of High Hall.Mrs.Gibson owns about 500 acres of land.She has two lodgers in High Hallwhere she has lived for over 20 years. The church in Stanbridge is called St.Kenelm's and was closed three years ago because very few people came to worship.It is built of flint stone. The garage in Stanbridge has petrol pumps and an M.O.T. bay.Cars do not use the garage often,probably because there are several garages in Wimborne Minster.
